metadata.name: Updraft #68
metadata.description:
UPDRAFT seeks to reproduce the beauty of tornadoes and other vortices in a minimalist style and simple shapes, thus highlighting the purity of the lines of these fascinating objects.

If the tornado of life scares you, remember that while you will probably be a little shaken and confused on your journey, you will end up at the top of it. That's the beauty of the updraft.

[S] or [Double-Tap] when viewing in full screen to save a 4000x4000 PNG image

Artist: Estienne
August 2022
Made with p5.js
Best viewed on Chrome or Chromium-based browsers

metadata.name: Chaosplot #105
metadata.description:
Continued exploration of the algorithm from "Chaospill" with a symmetric two tone style that is plotter friendly. The result can be rotated to whatever orientation works best for your display purposes. The code is presented unminified with comments and will be open sourced soon.

Live Mode Controls

Click to regenerate with a different starting seed.
1 - Save a SVG, the result is sized for 11"x17" prints with each color on a separate layer
2 - Save a PNG of the output
3 - Switch paper size to 8.5"x11" letter or A1 for different size plots
4 - Toggle HD mode which increases resolution and disables noise for printing

Code and Outputs are Copyright (C) 2022 Frank Force - Artwork is released under CC BY-NC 4.0.

metadata.name: THE400FLIPS #335
metadata.description:
The more they flip. The more you’ll make.

p5.js –> Blockchain


Controls:

[s] save as PNG.
[a] render alternate higher resolution artwork (takes a few seconds).
[z] save alternate artwork as PNG.


Artist note:

Primary royalties are split 95-5% between artist and The Processing Foundation.

Secondary royalties go to the minters (99.9% of the 15%).

The preview thumbnails don’t do justice to the artworks. Please run the code to appreciate them better. Also, remember to check the alternate higher resolution renders using [a].

Some preview thumbnails might look slightly different to the artwork seen when running the code. This is due to the resolution difference between the capture module and the live code on your device. 

Please get in touch in the event of a blank preview thumbnail. 

Made in p5.js and rendered in webGL. Tested on Chrome and Safari.


Copyright (©) 2022 Thomas Noya
Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Block Explorer #13
metadata.description:
Block Explorer is a playable piece of generative art.

Created as a collection of unique animated pieces of art with a camera flying through an endless stream of blocks, Block Explorer is also a playful experience pushing the boundaries of interactions in generative art.

How to use :
* Just click to enter the auto art mode.
* Press the space bar to enter the playable mode and take control over the camera. Make your own way and explore as many blocks as you can.
* Press « i » on the home screen to access infos and set a username.


———————
www.ferdinanddervieux.com/BlockExplorer

Block Explorer by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022

metadata.name: Los Osos 2422 #2367
metadata.description:
# Los Osos 2422

I was working on the next EmProps release when accidentally I opened a link to a bear utopic civilization through their existing metaverse. Or should I say "metabears"?

Enter Los Osos 2422. 

Four hundred years into the future bears live in a peaceful civilization heavily inspired by the generative art movement of our times. They are organized in districts that are sustained by bamboo, salmon, berries, and art! Los Osos are black, grizzly, panda, and polar, yet there are no distinctions between species; it's not like they were humans. 

They have different occupations but frequently bears change jobs giving birth to the most eclectic looks.

I took my sketchbook out to capture what I could and started drawing but my presence pissed them off. Ninjas, luchadores, and even a cybearpunk forced me to escape.  Is that a live gummy bear or am I just hungry? The story will continue...

-- 

Los Osos 2422 is a PFP art piece composed of 320 hand-made drawings made as an homage to the nascent generative art current fueled by Tezos blockchain technology in 2022. It features hundreds of references to artists and pieces in several generative and non-generative fields.

The project combines the assets together using a custom open-source algorithm that allows them to stack with the positioning in front and behind the character to create possibilities like shirt collars or hats, dynamic tinting to have hoodies or glasses with different colors, exceptions to give them laser eyes or a green apple in front of the face, complex set-ups to have different versions for some of the outfits, and chance control to allow precise control over the features.

--

Press 'S' on the keyboard to save it as an 1800 x 1800 pixels PNG.
